  "text": "Previous reports recommended ciprofloxacin as the most effective agent against Salmonella PJIs [CITATION_1] . However, with the increased virulence of the organism and the emergence of new resistant strains, it became important to perform in vitro sensitivity testing for each individual case. Studies have shown that various antimicrobial agents, including ampicillin, chloramphenicol, trimethoprim-sulfamethoxazole and third-generation cephalosporins, are valid options for treatment of different strains [CITATION_2] .",
